I mean, I just... This is great.
I think... I think it'll really help.

01:06:00.355 --> 01:06:02.289
I feel like you are exactly what he needs.

01:06:02.357 --> 01:06:03.381
<i>Well, thank you.</i>

01:06:03.458 --> 01:06:05.619
<i>- Does that make sense?
- Yes, it does.</i>

01:06:07.562 --> 01:06:10.861
<i>- Graham Claydon. Thank you.
- At your service.</i>

01:06:12.067 --> 01:06:15.161
All we need is a place for them to meet
and rehearse, like an apartment.

01:06:15.270 --> 01:06:17.261
You're asking for an apartment
for Nathaniel?

01:06:17.338 --> 01:06:20.432
- Yeah.
- Does he want an apartment? Thanks.

01:06:20.508 --> 01:06:24.103
- Yes.
- And he told you this?

01:06:24.179 --> 01:06:27.080
- Yes.
- You're so full of shit, Lopez.

01:06:27.549 --> 01:06:29.744
- I don't want an apartment.
- Good, 'cause it's not.

01:06:29.818 --> 01:06:31.251
It's actually a music studio

01:06:31.319 --> 01:06:33.150
for Mr. Claydon to give you
the cello lessons.

01:06:33.221 --> 01:06:35.121
Well, why don't we have Mr. Claydon
come down here?

01:06:35.190 --> 01:06:36.316
This is a perfect place to play in,
the tunnel.

01:06:36.391 --> 01:06:37.380
No, Mr. Claydon doesn't like tunnels.

01:06:37.459 --> 01:06:38.949
We'll just have Mr. Claydon come here
to do the lesson.

01:06:39.027 --> 01:06:40.426
- He says it has to be quiet.
- Well...

01:06:40.495 --> 01:06:42.690
It has to be quiet for the cello lessons,
so your apartment...

01:06:42.764 --> 01:06:43.788
It's not my apartment.

01:06:43.865 --> 01:06:45.765
I know. I know. The apartment
that belongs to no one.

01:06:45.834 --> 01:06:47.665
I don't have an apartment.
I don't wanna be in an apartment.

01:06:47.736 --> 01:06:48.828
I don't need an apartment.

01:06:48.903 --> 01:06:50.063
Beethoven lives out
in the freshness of the air.

01:06:50.138 --> 01:06:51.162
Nathaniel, the apartment
is not the point.

01:06:51.239 --> 01:06:52.501
He's the leader of Los Angeles.

01:06:52.574 --> 01:06:54.474
- It's an opportunity.
- "Angeles" means "angels. " You can't...

01:06:54.542 --> 01:06:56.203
- You can't hold down angels.
- Do you want the opportunity?

01:06:56.277 --> 01:06:57.266
- You can't clip angels.
- Stop.

01:06:57.345 --> 01:07:01.179
- Do you want an opportunity or not?
- Do you have an apartment?

01:07:05.620 --> 01:07:07.850
No. I have a house.

01:07:16.498 --> 01:07:19.524
So angry. Yelling.

01:07:20.502 --> 01:07:22.436
It doesn't make sense.

01:07:46.127 --> 01:07:48.618
- Do you have a family?
- What?

01:07:48.696 --> 01:07:50.664
Are you a married man?

01:07:52.033 --> 01:07:54.263
- Is there a Mrs. Steve Lopez?
- No.

01:07:56.104 --> 01:08:00.336
I did. Mary. But we split up.

01:08:02.010 --> 01:08:05.343
We have a son, Thomas.
He's in college now.

01:08:05.413 --> 01:08:09.076
Mr. Steve Lopez, Mr. Thomas
Steve Lopez, Mrs. Mary Steve Lopez.

01:08:09.150 --> 01:08:13.052
Not Mrs. Lopez. Mary Weston.

01:08:13.121 --> 01:08:17.921
- Mrs. Mary Weston Steve Lopez.
- No. Just Mary Weston. Period.

01:08:17.992 --> 01:08:21.984
We were married. We're not anymore,
so now she's just Mary.

01:08:22.063 --> 01:08:25.999
You were married to Mary,
but you're not married to Mary anymore.

01:08:26.067 --> 01:08:29.036
Correct. Don't ask me how.

01:08:31.406 --> 01:08:35.035
Mrs. Floria Ayers, Miss Jennifer Ayers.

01:08:35.109 --> 01:08:37.872
And then there was
Mr. Nathaniel Anthony Ayers Sr.

01:08:37.946 --> 01:08:40.176
He was a big man. He had big hands.

01:08:40.247 --> 01:08:43.479
I have very small hands.

01:08:43.551 --> 01:08:46.349
Fit around a violin, a cello.

01:08:48.957 --> 01:08:51.948
Mr. Ayers was a big man,
but he wasn't a god.

01:08:53.895 --> 01:08:55.920
I have my god.

01:08:55.997 --> 01:08:57.395
Mr. Steve Lopez.

01:08:57.465 --> 01:08:58.453
Oh, boy.

01:08:58.533 --> 01:09:00.023
Yeah, you're my god.
Flying around high.

01:09:00.100 --> 01:09:01.796
- You're my god.
- I'm not comfortable being your god.

01:09:01.870 --> 01:09:03.167
Mr. Steve Lopez, staff writer,
you are my god.

01:09:03.238 --> 01:09:04.899
- That it? I'm your god?
- Yes, you are. You're my god.

01:09:04.973 --> 01:09:07.305
All right. I am your god.

01:09:07.375 --> 01:09:08.865
And as your god,

01:09:08.943 --> 01:09:11.844
I command you to be at Lamp,
2:00 p. m., one week from today

01:09:11.912 --> 01:09:15.212
for a cello lesson. Done deal.

01:09:18.286 --> 01:09:20.481
And it's a really sweet deal, too.

01:09:20.555 --> 01:09:22.886
'Cause if you show up,
I will grant you eternal life.

01:09:22.957 --> 01:09:25.585
Hell, I might even make you a disciple.

01:09:25.660 --> 01:09:28.322
If you don't, you're on your own.

01:09:29.997 --> 01:09:31.225
<i>This is my apartment.
This is my apartment.</i>

01:09:31.299 --> 01:09:32.663
<i>This is my apartment.</i>

01:09:32.734 --> 01:09:34.224
<i>This is my apartment.
This is my apartment.</i>

01:09:34.301 --> 01:09:35.496
<i>This is my apartment.</i>

01:09:35.569 --> 01:09:36.696
<i>Always number one.
Always number two.</i>

01:09:36.770 --> 01:09:37.897
<i>Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:37.971 --> 01:09:39.599
<i>We've always been here,
Nathaniel Ayers.</i>

01:09:39.674 --> 01:09:42.006
<i>I've always been with you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:42.076 --> 01:09:45.045
<i>I'll never leave you, Nathaniel.
I love you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:45.113 --> 01:09:47.138
<i>- I love you.
- No one else loves you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:47.215 --> 01:09:49.944
<i>But I love you, Nathaniel.
I'll protect you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:50.018 --> 01:09:53.078
<i>When you fell from Heaven,
they laughed at you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:53.154 --> 01:09:56.715
<i>You're my heart, Nathaniel.
I do love you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:56.791 --> 01:09:58.918
<i>We'll be together forever, Nathaniel.</i>

01:09:58.993 --> 01:10:00.017
<i>I'll protect you.</i>

01:10:00.094 --> 01:10:01.994
<i>Look, I'll be here
to protect you from the pain.</i>

01:10:02.063 --> 01:10:05.123
<i>- I'll be here to protect you from the pain.
- Fibber. You fibber. You fib.</i>

01:10:05.199 --> 01:10:06.496
<i>I'll protect you from the noise.</i>

01:10:06.567 --> 01:10:08.000
Fear for you. Fear for you.

01:10:08.069 --> 01:10:09.696
<i>I'll protect you from their beady eyes.</i>

01:10:09.771 --> 01:10:11.830
<i>- I'll be here to obey.
- I'll protect you from their eyes.</i>

01:10:13.908 --> 01:10:15.967
<i>- Step right, Nathaniel.
- No one else loves you, Nathaniel.</i>

01:10:16.044 --> 01:10:17.568
<i>You're my boy, Nathaniel.</i>

01:10:17.645 --> 01:10:20.307
<i>- Take off the shoes.
- I'll protect you. I'll protect you.</i>

01:10:20.381 --> 01:10:22.611
No one can kill the child.
That's what the child is about.

01:10:22.684 --> 01:10:23.878
Forget you. Jump off!

01:10:43.204 --> 01:10:44.193
Come on.

01:10:45.440 --> 01:10:47.635
Hey. Look at that.

01:10:49.210 --> 01:10:52.145
Don't see those on the street.
Quick right.

01:10:53.448 --> 01:10:55.109
And then, and then...
And then right again, right here.

01:10:55.183 --> 01:10:58.346
Nathaniel. Come on down.

01:10:58.419 --> 01:11:02.913
What are you... Come on. We go down
here and then to the end and left.

01:11:02.991 --> 01:11:04.515
I think we should do the lesson out here.

01:11:04.592 --> 01:11:06.958
No, no, no. It's just this way. Come on.

01:11:07.028 --> 01:11:09.155
Mr. Lopez... Mr. Lopez.

01:11:09.230 --> 01:11:11.221
Mr. Lopez, I really think
we should do it out here.

01:11:11.299 --> 01:11:14.325
No, come on. Let's have a look.
It's right down here.

01:11:14.402 --> 01:11:15.869
Mr. Lopez.

01:11:16.270 --> 01:11:18.033
Nathaniel, come on.

01:11:18.406 --> 01:11:20.101
It's really clean.

01:11:23.344 --> 01:11:25.141
Come check it out.

01:11:26.180 --> 01:11:30.412
We should do it out here. It's better.
I'm more comfortable out here.

01:11:35.256 --> 01:11:36.621
Looks nice.

01:11:38.793 --> 01:11:40.158
Looks nice.

01:11:45.433 --> 01:11:46.900
It's nice.

01:12:22.270 --> 01:12:24.329
Come on. You can do it.

01:12:49.097 --> 01:12:50.359
Hey.

01:12:54.936 --> 01:12:56.062
I can't live here.

01:12:56.137 --> 01:12:58.537
I'll give you a hand with that.

01:13:01.375 --> 01:13:02.569
Got it.

01:13:04.779 --> 01:13:07.270
Oh, boy. Let's get this in nice.

01:13:10.318 --> 01:13:11.376
Good.

01:13:16.691 --> 01:13:17.715
It's great, right?

01:13:17.792 --> 01:13:20.386
I mean, I like it. What do you think?

01:13:22.497 --> 01:13:25.796
It's nice. It's clean.
The bathroom's better than...

01:13:28.002 --> 01:13:29.526
Except for him.

01:13:29.604 --> 01:13:31.231
I don't wanna die in here.

01:13:31.305 --> 01:13:32.567
Don't...

01:13:32.640 --> 01:13:33.732
Somebody could just come in here
and kill me...

01:13:33.808 --> 01:13:35.708
- You'll be fine. Nathaniel?
... and take all of my belongings.

01:13:35.776 --> 01:13:37.300
- Nathaniel, the door locks.
- A fly only lives 12 days.

01:13:37.378 --> 01:13:39.972
What if in 12 days, someone walks
through that door and murders me?

01:13:40.047 --> 01:13:41.742
And I don't care
about this Claydon thing, either.

01:13:41.816 --> 01:13:43.647
Walt Disney Hall. Disney Duck.

01:13:43.718 --> 01:13:45.015
Doesn't make a difference.
I don't need any of that.

01:13:45.086 --> 01:13:47.145
If I'm gonna take a lesson,
I should take the lesson in the tunnel

01:13:47.221 --> 01:13:50.156
where I can hear the city sounds
and not be locked off from life,

01:13:50.224 --> 01:13:51.350
locked off from the world.

01:13:51.425 --> 01:13:53.723
In the tunnel I can hear the music
the way it's supposed to be played.

01:13:53.794 --> 01:13:55.318
Not in this place, there's no city sounds,

01:13:55.396 --> 01:13:58.058
there's no Beethoven,
there's no Los Angeles, California.

01:13:58.132 --> 01:13:59.622
I don't belong here.

01:13:59.700 --> 01:14:01.031
I'm never coming here again.

01:14:32.133 --> 01:14:34.124
Nathaniel, that's Graham Claydon.

01:14:35.803 --> 01:14:37.532
Pleased to meet you, Nathaniel.

01:14:38.839 --> 01:14:41.569
I always love meeting a fellow musician.

01:14:44.145 --> 01:14:46.113
I brought you something.

01:14:46.314 --> 01:14:49.010
I know you're partial to Beethoven,

01:14:49.083 --> 01:14:51.643
so I thought you'd enjoy this,

01:14:52.420 --> 01:14:57.323
because, you know,
without Johann Sebastian

01:14:57.391 --> 01:15:00.622
there would be no Ludwig van.

01:15:16.310 --> 01:15:19.279
The A, the D, the A, the D, the A, the D.

01:15:21.182 --> 01:15:23.810
Steady. Don't rush it. Don't rush it.

01:15:29.824 --> 01:15:31.121
And...

01:15:35.529 --> 01:15:37.520
Well, for someone who hasn't had
a lesson in three decades,

01:15:37.598 --> 01:15:39.691
you play quite beautifully.

01:15:40.134 --> 01:15:41.328
Thank you.

01:15:41.402 --> 01:15:42.596
- So...
- Thank you.

01:15:42.703 --> 01:15:45.228
Work on a smoother rhythm
with the right hand.

01:15:45.306 --> 01:15:47.797
And don't stop-start.

01:15:47.875 --> 01:15:50.366
Carry a phrase all the way through.

01:15:50.611 --> 01:15:51.600
- Great.
- Give you a ride uptown?

01:15:51.712 --> 01:15:53.202
- Thank you.
- Mr. Claydon?

01:15:54.081 --> 01:15:55.981
- Yes.
- Sir?

01:15:57.885 --> 01:16:00.376
Do you think I could be good again?

01:16:02.556 --> 01:16:04.046
Yes, I do.

01:16:06.961 --> 01:16:09.486
I like your apartment, by the way.

01:16:09.897 --> 01:16:11.421
- It's not my apartment.
- It's not. It's just a...

01:16:11.499 --> 01:16:12.659
I don't live here.

01:16:13.034 --> 01:16:14.296
Well, you should.

01:16:15.836 --> 01:16:19.567
God has blessed you
with a gift, Nathaniel.

01:16:19.640 --> 01:16:22.871
Nothing pains God more
than when we squander his blessings.

01:16:23.144 --> 01:16:25.612
- You owe it to him to care for this...
- I don't owe God.

01:16:28.049 --> 01:16:30.176
Mr. Steve Lopez is my god.

01:16:30.484 --> 01:16:32.145
- What?
- Star writer for Los Angeles.

01:16:32.219 --> 01:16:34.449
Higher power flying around
with wings like an angel.

01:16:34.522 --> 01:16:36.922
Mr. Steve Lopez is my...

01:16:37.558 --> 01:16:38.582
He doesn't know what he's saying.

01:16:38.659 --> 01:16:40.786
Mr. Graham Claydon is going to tell me
who my god is?

01:16:40.861 --> 01:16:41.850
Down by the car?

01:16:41.929 --> 01:16:43.157
Do you know who my god is,
Mr. Claydon?

01:16:43.297 --> 01:16:45.060
I know who my god is!

01:16:45.132 --> 01:16:46.156
- He's a good teacher.
- I know who my god is.

01:16:46.233 --> 01:16:47.495
You should accept his help gracefully.

01:16:47.568 --> 01:16:49.331
Graceful is the ballerinas at Juilliard.

01:16:49.770 --> 01:16:51.135
Those girls were graceful.

01:16:51.205 --> 01:16:53.833
- Tiny ballerinas just twirling round.
- There's other people in this...

01:16:54.775 --> 01:16:56.174
- Twirling round. Angels.
- All right,

01:16:56.243 --> 01:16:58.370
- graceful as little ballerinas.
- I love them flying around

01:16:58.446 --> 01:17:00.812
like I love Mr. Steve Lopez flying around.

01:17:00.881 --> 01:17:03.042
I love God. I love you!

01:17:10.124 --> 01:17:11.455
I love you.

01:17:14.729 --> 01:17:15.855
I don't want him to love me.

01:17:15.930 --> 01:17:18.091
Well, it looks like
you might have to get over that.

01:17:18.165 --> 01:17:19.427
It's a bad idea.

01:17:19.500 --> 01:17:21.468
"I love you, Steve,"
turns into, "You failed me, Steve,"

01:17:21.535 --> 01:17:23.366
turns into very bad things.

01:17:23.437 --> 01:17:25.598
That's my limited experience.

01:17:25.773 --> 01:17:28.298
I don't want to be on the other side
of that with him. Would you?

01:17:28.376 --> 01:17:31.436
He doesn't know if I'm a ballerina,
if I'm God, if I'm an airplane pilot.

01:17:31.512 --> 01:17:34.003
He has no idea what he's saying.

01:17:35.282 --> 01:17:37.409
Is there something you want
from me, Lopez?

01:17:37.618 --> 01:17:39.745
Or did you just come to show me
your prom dress? You look nice.

01:17:39.820 --> 01:17:40.809
I want you to help him

01:17:41.155 --> 01:17:42.679
because he's sick
and he needs medication

01:17:42.757 --> 01:17:44.486
and you have a team of doctors here.

01:17:44.558 --> 01:17:46.958
Tell them to sit down with him.
Isn't that what you're supposed to do?

01:17:47.395 --> 01:17:49.989
Nathaniel's made it quite clear
he's not ready to speak to a psychiatrist.

01:17:50.064 --> 01:17:51.053
Force him.

01:17:51.198 --> 01:17:52.256
- Force him?
- Tell him to do it.

01:17:52.333 --> 01:17:53.391
Tell him he can't play his instruments

01:17:53.467 --> 01:17:54.491
until he sits down with a shrink.

01:17:54.568 --> 01:17:58.060
- That's not what we do here.
- What you do here is fucked.

01:18:00.174 --> 01:18:01.334
It is.

01:18:02.276 --> 01:18:07.475
Look, even if I did wanna
cohorse Nathaniel into psychiatry...

01:18:07.548 --> 01:18:08.913
- Coerce.
... which... Whatever.

01:18:08.983 --> 01:18:10.746
- Coerce.
- Lf I wanted to do that, which I don't,

01:18:10.818 --> 01:18:13.582
I couldn't force him to take medication.

01:18:13.654 --> 01:18:15.918
The law is the law.
Unless he's an imminent danger

01:18:15.990 --> 01:18:17.787
to himself or someone else...

01:18:17.858 --> 01:18:19.849
Are you gonna answer that, or what?

01:18:24.832 --> 01:18:27.300
I'm in the car. What if he was
a danger to someone else?

01:18:27.368 --> 01:18:31.099
- But he's not.
- Mary, I'm on the way. Relax.

01:18:31.172 --> 01:18:33.367
What if someone said he was?

01:18:33.441 --> 01:18:35.568
What if someone dialed 911
and said Nathaniel had attacked him?

01:18:35.643 --> 01:18:36.667
They'd put him in psychiatric hospital.

01:18:36.744 --> 01:18:38.644
I know you're not thinking
of lying on him, Lopez.

01:18:38.712 --> 01:18:40.703
And then he would be
in a 14-day psychiatric hold,

01:18:40.781 --> 01:18:43.375
they'd put him on meds straight away.

01:18:43.784 --> 01:18:46.252
What if that's all it took
for him to be well?

01:18:46.320 --> 01:18:48.720
What if two weeks of meds,
a two-week window

01:18:48.789 --> 01:18:53.419
into what his life could be,
changed his life? Saved his life?

01:18:54.295 --> 01:18:56.820
Why wouldn't you want to be
part of that?

01:18:58.265 --> 01:19:02.929
Steve, Nathaniel has one thing going
for him right now. A friend.

01:19:04.004 --> 01:19:08.441
If you betray that friendship, you destroy
the only thing he has in this world.

01:19:08.509 --> 01:19:10.977
I don't want to be his only thing.

01:19:17.151 --> 01:19:19.517
Didn't you just tell somebody
you was in your car?

01:19:25.192 --> 01:19:27.023
Mary, relax. What table are we at?

01:19:27.094 --> 01:19:29.221
<i>This is Nathaniel Anthony Ayers, Jr.,
Mr. Lopez. I was calling...</i>

01:19:29.296 --> 01:19:30.490
- Nathaniel.
... because you promised me

01:19:30.564 --> 01:19:32.759
a hard case for my cello
and I haven't received it yet.

01:19:32.833 --> 01:19:34.664
<i>- Yeah?
- And also I need sheet music</i>

01:19:34.735 --> 01:19:36.134
<i>for Beethoven's Second Sonata.</i>

01:19:36.203 --> 01:19:39.866
<i>And also Opus 131 and Septet for
strings and woodwinds, and Opus 20...</i>

01:19:39.940 --> 01:19:41.999
Can you just... One sec.

01:19:42.076 --> 01:19:44.977
<i>- ... and also my A string is missing...
- So, we're talking about...</i>

01:19:45.045 --> 01:19:47.479
I need my A string replaced.

01:19:47.548 --> 01:19:50.415
Nathaniel, you know, this is not...

01:19:53.087 --> 01:19:56.181
<i>...his series in the Times
on the struggles and the triumphs</i>

01:19:56.257 --> 01:19:58.452
<i>of Nathaniel Anthony Ayers</i>

01:19:58.526 --> 01:20:01.859
<i>has brought crucial attention to one
of the most pressing issues in our city.</i>

01:20:01.929 --> 01:20:03.556
<i>...promises you should make good
on those promises...</i>

01:20:03.631 --> 01:20:05.155
Get off the phone.

01:20:05.232 --> 01:20:07.996
<i>...to address this problem
with compassion and commitment.</i>

01:20:08.068 --> 01:20:09.092
<i>And in honor of this,</i>

01:20:09.169 --> 01:20:13.367
<i>it is my pleasure to present this year's
Media Award to Steve Lopez.</i>

01:20:15.009 --> 01:20:16.306
Thank you.

01:20:19.446 --> 01:20:21.914
<i>...you know that I can't leave
my cart anywhere.</i>

01:20:21.982 --> 01:20:25.577
<i>It houses my violin, my cello,
and my weapons of mass destruction.</i>

01:20:25.653 --> 01:20:28.645
<i>A child needs protection. You don't want
to put a baby in the trunk of a car</i>

01:20:28.722 --> 01:20:30.883
