01:39:08.608 --> 01:39:09.905
A stranger.

01:39:11.310 --> 01:39:12.470
And...

01:39:13.946 --> 01:39:16.574
I don't know who to fault.

01:39:16.649 --> 01:39:21.848
I can't see any outcome to support.

01:39:26.559 --> 01:39:29.187
Can't believe in anything worthwhile.

01:39:33.066 --> 01:39:36.433
Done trying. I resign. I resign.

01:39:37.370 --> 01:39:39.031
From everything.

01:39:39.639 --> 01:39:41.607
It's... It's official.

01:39:49.315 --> 01:39:51.715
You couldn't stop that earthquake.

01:39:57.223 --> 01:40:00.420
You can't fix LA in just...

01:40:02.128 --> 01:40:04.756
And you're never gonna cure Nathaniel.

01:40:10.036 --> 01:40:12.596
Just be his friend and show up.

01:41:33.920 --> 01:41:36.650
Good? I'll be right here if you need me.

01:41:49.068 --> 01:41:51.036
...go, next to the gold store.

01:41:51.103 --> 01:41:53.833
You know what I mean.
He wanted to drink and everything.

01:41:53.906 --> 01:41:56.101
Okay, okay, okay. Bitch, slow down.

01:41:56.976 --> 01:42:01.106
Do you still love me?
Like you did at the start?

01:42:01.180 --> 01:42:02.909
I ain't playing with you.

01:42:02.982 --> 01:42:05.075
I'm saying I do.

01:42:05.151 --> 01:42:07.847
It means you and me together forever.

01:42:09.655 --> 01:42:13.523
So that's why I'm saying I do.

01:42:15.027 --> 01:42:18.360
- I love you, Lois.
- I love you, too, Darryl.

01:42:21.133 --> 01:42:24.660
Disguise himself now as...

01:42:24.737 --> 01:42:29.504
They disguise themselves...
Where is Los Angeles?

01:42:29.976 --> 01:42:31.773
Cleveland?

01:42:35.147 --> 01:42:36.444
And...

01:43:01.440 --> 01:43:02.930
We...

01:43:08.581 --> 01:43:10.742
We had some life, didn't we?

01:43:14.420 --> 01:43:15.751
Yeah.

01:43:16.789 --> 01:43:18.017
Yeah.

01:44:02.568 --> 01:44:05.162
<i>Beethoven's Triple Concerto, right?</i>

01:44:05.671 --> 01:44:07.536
- Yeah.
- It's a good one.

01:44:09.875 --> 01:44:11.103
I liked it.

01:44:11.544 --> 01:44:15.480
Mr. Ayers, I'm gonna give your sister
a ride to the hotel.

01:44:15.548 --> 01:44:18.073
You don't have to
call me that, Mr. Lopez.

01:44:18.150 --> 01:44:22.177
I know. I want to. I should have been
calling you that all along.

01:44:22.822 --> 01:44:24.756
I said such terrible things
to you, Mr. Lopez.

01:44:24.824 --> 01:44:28.590
I... I hate myself for saying those things.

01:44:28.661 --> 01:44:31.152
Sometimes friends piss
each other off, right?

01:44:31.230 --> 01:44:33.095
It's part of the deal.

01:44:33.532 --> 01:44:39.300
I can't imagine that you would want to be
my friend after I said all those things.

01:44:39.438 --> 01:44:40.598
I just...

01:44:40.673 --> 01:44:42.004
Mr. Ayers,

01:44:44.276 --> 01:44:46.506
I'm honored to be your friend.

01:45:06.632 --> 01:45:08.691
<i>"Points West" by Steve Lopez.</i>

01:45:09.468 --> 01:45:12.062
<i>A year ago, I met a man
who was down on his luck</i>

01:45:12.138 --> 01:45:14.971
<i>and thought I might be able to help him.</i>

01:45:15.041 --> 01:45:17.009
<i>I don't know that I have.</i>

01:45:17.376 --> 01:45:19.742
<i>Yes, my friend Mr. Ayers
now sleeps inside.</i>

01:45:19.812 --> 01:45:22.372
<i>He has a key. He has a bed.</i>

01:45:23.516 --> 01:45:26.212
<i>But his mental state, and his well-being,</i>

01:45:26.285 --> 01:45:29.516
<i>are as precarious now
as they were the day we met.</i>

01:45:32.925 --> 01:45:35.723
<i>There are people who tell me
I've helped him.</i>

01:45:35.795 --> 01:45:38.059
<i>Mental health experts who say</i>

01:45:38.130 --> 01:45:42.430
<i>that the simple act of being someone's
friend can change his brain chemistry,</i>

01:45:42.501 --> 01:45:45.129
<i>improve his functioning in the world.</i>

01:45:45.905 --> 01:45:48.806
<i>I can't speak for Mr. Ayers
in that regard.</i>

01:45:49.075 --> 01:45:52.340
<i>Maybe our friendship has helped him.
But maybe not.</i>

01:45:54.847 --> 01:45:57.281
<i>I can, however, speak for myself.</i>

01:45:58.117 --> 01:46:01.553
<i>I can tell you that by witnessing
Mr. Ayers's courage,</i>

01:46:02.021 --> 01:46:05.957
<i>his humility, his faith
in the power of his art,</i>

01:46:08.094 --> 01:46:11.860
<i>I've learned the dignity of being loyal
to something you believe in.</i>

01:46:11.931 --> 01:46:15.230
<i>Of holding onto it, above all else.</i>

01:46:15.301 --> 01:46:20.466
<i>Of believing, without question,
that it will carry you home.</i>

